  "prompt": "Are there other movies like The Secret?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several movies similar to \"The Secret\" that focus on positive thinking, personal development, and the law of attraction:\n\n1. \"What the Bleep Do We Know!?\" (2004)\n- Explores quantum physics and consciousness\n- Similar metaphysical themes\n\n2. \"Think and Grow Rich\" (various adaptations)\n- Based on Napoleon Hill's self-help book\n- Focuses on manifestation and personal success\n\n3. \"The Opus\" (2008)\n- Produced by the same team behind \"The Secret\"\n- Discusses personal goal achievement\n\n4. \"The Moses Code\" (2008)\n- Spiritual documentary about manifestation\n- Explores metaphysical concepts\n\n5. \"You Can Heal Your Life\" (2007)\n- Based on Louise Hay's book\n- Emphasizes positive thinking and self-healing\n\n6. \"Manifesting with Esther Hicks\" (Multiple documentaries)\n- Features Abraham-Hicks teachings\n- Discusses law of attraction principles\n\n7. \"The Power of Thought\" (Various documentaries)\n- Explores mind-body connection\n- Discusses visualization and positive thinking\n\nThese films share similar themes of personal empowerment, positive thinking, and the idea that mental attitude can influence life outcomes.",
